data.title: Manon
data.meta_description: Manon (1949) starring Serge Reggiani, Michel Auclair, Ccile Aubry and directed by Henri-Georges Clouzot.
data.text: Port of Marseille, France, recently liberated from the German yoke. Caught as stowaways aboard a ship, Manon, a young woman who was accused of collaborating with the Nazis, and Robert, a freedom fighter who saved her from reprisals, tell the captain about the many challenges they have had to face in order to survive.
